cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Órbita in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Órbita: Agentic Financial Assistant for Brazilian Young Adults"
abstract: >
  Órbita is an academic proof-of-concept agentic financial assistant built with
  LangGraph, FAISS, and Ollama. It provides citation-backed financial literacy
  guidance for Brazilian young adults by indexing official BACEN/CVM sources and
  using a Self-RAG anti-hallucination pipeline. MCP integration with Pluggy
  enables Open Finance data access for automated expense categorization and
  goal deviation alerts.
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-03-12"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/orbita-project/orbita"
keywords:
  - financial-literacy
  - RAG
  - LangGraph
  - MCP
  - Brazil
  - open-finance
  - self-RAG
  - agentic-AI
